			section.about-why
				.about-why__container 
					h2 Why <span>alex sky ?</span>
					p.about-why__text-top We work to deliver the best possible combination of fair price and high service in the shipping industry. Alex Sky is a regional expert with a network in 48 states and we have the knowledge and resources to provide innovative, cost-effective shipping solutions every time you need it.
					.about-why__blocks(class="flex")
						.about-why__block
							h3 Alex Sky’s mission is to provide:
							.about-why__text <h4>1) High service</h4>We seek to provide our customers with the best logistics services in the industry and respond and fulfill customer requests as soon as possible.
							.about-why__text <h4>2) Smart price</h4>Alex Sky provides affordable delivery services to our customers.
							.about-why__text <h4>3) Integrity and Honesty</h4>We keep our customers informed at all times.<br>When we run into delays or any problems, we strive to be open, honest and work it out in a fair and professional manner.
							.about-why__text <h4>4) Safety</h4>We pay high attention to safety in all aspects of our operations by empowering all of our employees and employing professional drivers.
						.about-why__block
							h3 Our advantages:
							ul 
								li Extensive experience in the US 
								li Steady track record of consistent and profitable growth
								li Experienced and fully equipped drivers
								li 2 full service regional terminals
								li A progressive and entrepreneurial culture
								li Serving companies of all sizes
					p.about-why__text-bottom No matter what direction your business takes you or what you need to ship, Alex Sky will cover you. Our innovative transportation and experience will help optimize your supply chain at every turn. We have the flexibility and different services to meet any change in your supply chain. In our fleet we have dry vans, reefers and flatbeds which can handle many types of delivery.
			section.about-history
				.about-history__container 
					h2 Our <span>history</span>
					.history__blocks
						.history__blocks-absolute
						.history__block-one
							.flex 
								.history__block-title 2016
								.line 
							.history__block-text
								p Later this year our firm came with the company's first client as an independent shipping company. Reputation of our firm grew with this partnership.
								p Demand for our services grew fast and we hired the first employee to help us deal with the financial side of our business. 
						.history__block-two
							.flex 
								.history__block-title 2017
								.line 
							.history__block-text
								p Four more employees were brought on board. Considering customer convenience, Alex Sky opened a new terminal and repair shop in Jacksonville FL. It helped to ease drop-off and pick-up access for customers in the area.
								p Our family grew as well. Alex Sky relocated to an office space to accommodate the addition of an accountant and new sales agent.
								p This year we increased our customer base and bought some new trucks.
						.history__block-three
							.flex 
								.history__block-title 2018
								.line 
							.history__block-text
								p Growth of our company continued with the hiring of dispatchers, logistics coordinators and drivers.
								p Alex Sky started looking for new ways to make the cargo shipping services more efficient and easier for consumers.  To evolve our digital services, we formed partnerships with some software developers. Our mission was to push the limits of modern technology to make clients' experience more pleasant and effective.
						.history__block-four
							.flex 
								.history__block-title 2019
								.line 
							.history__block-text
								p Several new corporate moving and relocation companies began leveraging Alex Sky expertise, spurring growth of 21% for the company’s services.
								p The reputation of the company continues to extend with growing numbers of clients. Customers include thousands of satisfied corporate clients as well as individuals.
								p Our family continued to grow too. We hired more drivers for our trucks and owner operators as well as sales agents and marketer.
						.history__block-five
							.flex 
								.history__block-title 2020
								.line 
							.history__block-text
								p This year we broke our records with a 31% increase in retail bookings.
								p Alex Sky opens a terminal and repair shop in Chicago. Strong demand for shipping goods from Illinois to other States provided us the opportunity to set up a fully staffed trucking operation in Chicago. This operation allowed customers to take better control on moving freight between Illinois and Florida.
								p This year we bought some new trucks, including Dry Van, Reefer and Flatbed hoping to meet clients' growing demand.
						.history__block-six
							.flex 
								.history__block-title 2021
								.line 
							.history__block-text
								p We delivered over 150,000 cargo and demand continues to grow.
								p Alex Sky changed company policy to offer remote work to keep employees safe during the pandemic. Productivity remained steady and both the retail and business-to-business lines KPI kept growing.
								p This year we moved our headquarters from Jacksonville FL to Chicago IL, creating an office space with conference rooms, workstations and lounge area.
